One of us had sticky hands and laughed about it getting on their fork and he swooped by a few minutes later with a replacement. Needless to say service was terrific. The menu has a nice small selection of things but all we ordered was done really well. I had a grain bowl with tofu, we also had sesame wings and avocado toast. I have never paid so much for such poor service. The wait staff was the epitome of inefficiency, combined with an insultingly cavalier attitude.  We (party of two) were second in line to be seated (behind a party of 3) when we got to Friedman's on a Sunday afternoon past two. As we waited in line, we noticed there were a couple tables open (but not bussed) and even more were opening up as parties were paying and leaving. Yet, the lackadaisical attitude of the wait staff meant they couldn't be bothered to buss or prepare any of these free tables for waiting parties. Consequently, we ended up waiting for close to 20min before we were seated (the initial estimate we were given was 10min) and this too only after the hostess stepped in to buss and prepare some tables.  Once seated, the guy that was waiting on us was noticeably more attentive to tables on either side of us (not sure if this was because he was racist). He didn't return our greeting when we sat down, said not a single word when we plonked the water carafe down on our table, and proceeded to take orders from a table seated shortly after us first though clearly myself and my partner were ready to order. He then took his sweet time bringing out our drinks which meant he put our food order in later than the the afore-mentioned party that had arrived after us. It only got worse from here as our food was not brought out while that of two other parties that had been seated after we'd put in our food orders were brought out (there was no question of our orders being more complicated as one of these parties had the same orders as us).  After asking the server where our food was, he disappeared off into the kitchen, without a word of apology or explanation to us, and it took him a good time more to finally bring out our orders. Again, unaccompanied by any explanation or apology. Once served, he didn't bother checking in with us until after we'd asked for the check.  While our experience may have been limited to one particularly incompetent, rude, and potentially racist staff member, it was bad enough that we will not be returning to this place.  A pity, because the food itself was really good. Management should take notice, as this is sure to affect their business eventually.

So I took a friend here for lunch and was HIGHLY DISAPPOINTED with the food!!! So we get seated, the table is clean we get menus and greeted. Looking around its nicely decorated and put together beautifully. I see all the food rushing out from the kitchen its looks delicious and fresh. The chicken looks awesomely crispy and fried. I go over the menu and spot what I see constantly coming from the kitchen which is a fried chicken sandwich. So we're greeted to place our orders and I order the chicken sandwich that looks so good. I order it PLAIN, NOTHING ON IT... NOTHING... I also ask if fries comes with it I'm no so I ordered a side of fries and then my friend orders their food... Food comes and my order is wrong it comes fully loaded with everything its supposed to come with and fries and then a side of fries and then my friend's order, I'm trying to call the server over we get heavily ignored because the server was facing the wall at the ordering machine the whole time zoned in not turning around for anything. Finally another server sees me and this is now 3mins of trying to get our original server's attention.. ::side note:: I know that may sound like "Oooh I'm 'rushy" and a "right now" type of person but a 1hr lunch break goes by fast and time is a factor... back to my experience: so new server corrects all my food and the bill I now only have about 20mins to eat and head back to work. As I'm eating I see pink in the sandwich I kinda freak out because I thought it was a chicken breast white meat sandwich and they might be every now and  then but mine was dark meat. It also wasn't seasoned and it was the most blandest thing I've ever had. The fries were good and crispy. I didn't like the ketchup I guess they make a ketchup thats fresh and since I'm honestly so use to Heinz ketchup which I understand why they don't use it or won't use it since this is a farm to table like place but it had this off putting floral tangy taste with the fries. But I know that could just be me lol... so I'll just say that.. Lastly we had to ask for the check about 4x we get it and theres another problem. My friend's order was the special of the day they were promoting which was a burger and beer. And we were being charged for the special and then another beer when it was only 1. I think it was someone's 1st day and I can get that but the taste for me was the biggest thing and how honestly simple my order was and it was still wrong. Beautiful place and fresh food but the taste presented were just not there for me including the flavor it was just nothing BLAND BLAND BLAND... No thank you. Please update your menu to say those sandwiches come white or dark meat. Give an option please or say to expect either or meat cause that threw me so off from the piece of chicken I had, the piece just wasn't good and quite a bit of fat and really dark parts. But it was pretty before I ate it... lol.. anyways you guys need to add flavor give me at least some salt, pepper or some lemon for it... not even garlic!!! Come on guys fresh doesn't mean bland.. sauce doesn't cut it.. I know this is not popeye's or kfc, I know this isn't fast good fried food but theres is no excuse this was bland!!! Do more!!! First time visit of this small, family-friendly restaurant. Had a brunch on Saturday at 11:00 a.m. and the place was about 70~80% full already – seems to be a popular eatery for locals.  Food: the fried chicken & cheddar waffle was outstanding – the skin was crisp, non-greasy, tasty with just a pinch of spice while the inside was tender and moist. Pairing the savory fried chickens with hot cheddar waffle that was crispy outside and airy inside and you got an amazing dish! This is one of those dishes seems simple but actually is hard to perfect; in this case I think Firedman’s executes well and hits all the right notes.  Service: waiting staffs were courteous, professional and efficient. The wait-time between order placed (two main courses plus one side) and foods-on-the-table took about 20 minutes, which I consider it was reasonable.  Atmosphere: Given that this is a small restaurant with tight space, I won’t be surprised that the noise, or the energy level one might argue, could be high while it’s crowded. If you are looking for a bit quiet or intimate dining experience, then this place may not be suitable for you.  Price: For brunch menu, the pricing is reasonable. Majority of the items are around $15 plus/minus $3. Sides are within $6 plus/minus $2 range.

The worse part is how loud this place was with the music, the loud coffee grinding machine and the conversations at every table you couldn't help but over hear everyone's conversation because the tables were so close to each other. I'm in my mid 20's so for me to complain about noise is unlike me.

Picked this place because it was close to Columbia, had decent reviews, and the pictures of the place looked nice. Upon entering, we were immediately disappointed. We asked the hostess if we could have a booth, and a man (who I’m assuming is the manager) chimes in and says “well we don’t normally give booths to parties less than 3, but I guess I can make an exception this time” (mind you, the place was empty with just one other couple in the restaurant). So, we sit down, start reviewing the menu — the menu is very small, the prices are high, and the food is mediocre. I paid $14 for two eggs, bacon, and burnt toast. My fiancé ordered the same, so we’re already sitting at $28. I ordered a coffee, which was another $3.50, and my fiancé got a Diet Coke (in a can, no less). Our bill at the end was $36 — the cost wouldn’t have been an issue, except for the fact that our server wasn’t exactly a ray of sunshine either. He acted very pretentious the entire time we were there (I’m assuming due to the booth situation, but who knows?), didn’t even ask us how the food was once it came out, nor did he give us our check once the meal was over. He had another waiter do it. Once again, the place wasn’t packed.  I have been a server for over nine years, so I understand the difficulties that come with the job. But when you have a manager being snotty right from the get-go, a server who acts like he doesn’t want to serve us, and then a mediocre breakfast that costs $36, it was pretty much the worst trifecta experience. Needless to say, I will not be returning to the Friedman’s in Morningside, nor will I try another location. The entire experience but a pretty bad taste in my mouth altogether.

Great food, friendly service, knowledgable staff, and vegan options-- Friedman's is a fantastic place for a work lunch or afternoon coffee meeting. Lots of seasonal options, as well, and the specialty cocktail menu is both delicious and affordable (by New York standards.)

I have seen some of the other locations around Manhattan, but this is the first one that I went to. I had the pastrami reuben with a side of the grilled asparagus. Because of allergy reasons, I ordered the sandwich without cheese. The pastrami was a bit on the salty side, but overall it was very good. The bread was toasted quite nicely. The sauerkraut and the russian dressing complemented the meat well. The side of grilled asparagus also lived up to my hopes. After squeezing on the charred lemon it came with, it was perfect. One thing that confused me was that they did not have any dessert options. I am not sure if this is only for a limited time, or if it is permanent. But overall, I enjoyed my experience and look forward to going back in the future.
